# Files assignment
In this assignment, you will read an json file and create a few csv files. 
1. Rename adoptions.json file as your_name_adoptions.json.   
2. Review the contents of the json file and understand its structure.
3. Create a function that prompts the user for a folder name where the json file is found and opens the data into a variable.  Make sure the function will have mechanism for error handling.
The first item in the json file is shown below.  The data lists books adopted in academic institutions.  Review the structure and you will find that each adoption record has multiple contacts,
one university, multiple adoptions, and multiple messages.
